Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative\n                        Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\n                    \u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Palagonia\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\"/>\n                        \u003C!--No inventory number found-->\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A rock-cut tomb (Tomb 15) in the Coste di S. Frebonia, consisting of an entry and single chamber, with inscriptions on two walls, of which this is the left-hand wall\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/2.html\">stone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.rock-face\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/211\">rock face\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--Need to see original Maniscalco publication in Kokalos 39-40 (2.1), 881-900 for tomb publication-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>The text is engraved on the left-hand wall as one enters the tomb, in a single line, from right to left, with two further large letters separated from the main text\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Letters of the archaic Greek alphabet: sigma rendered with a single wavy line; of the two alphas, one is regular, the other the arrow-head form 'alpha siculum'. Of the main group, qoppa is the tallest at 130 mm; of the two alphas, the regular is 170 mm, the sikel form 110 mm\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">up to 130\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"110\" atMost=\"170\">110-170\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\"/>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523927\" corresp=\"#findspot\">Palagonia\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.32955, 14.74474\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0650\" notAfter-custom=\"-0501\" evidence=\"archaeological-context\">Archaic (the tomb is dated by typology only to the 7th century or early 6th century BCE)\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" xml:id=\"findspot\" when=\"1990\">On the wall of Tomb 15 was identified in 1990 at the Coste di S. Febronia, near Palagonia\u003Cgeo cert=\"low\">37.32519, 14.76745\u003C/geo>\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- Grotta S. Febronia identified on IGT 1:25000, but exact location of Tomb 15 not identified -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" corresp=\"#findspot\">in situ\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                    \n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\